<item>
            <title>[CXF-4226] @Description on class level not &quot;inherited&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4226</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is really a minor one: if you define a resource via interface&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Description(title = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;My resource&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; AResource {


@GET
@Description(title = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;bar&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
Response foo();

}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and then implement it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;ResourceImpl &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;implements&lt;/span&gt; AResource{

@PathParam(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;protected&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; id;

@Context
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; HttpHeaders httpHeaders;
	
@Context
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;protected&lt;/span&gt; UriInfo uriInfo;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; Response foo(){
 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Response.ok().build();
}

}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Then the generated WADL document will contain the method description (&quot;bar&quot;) but not the resource level description (&quot;My resource&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Workaround: annotate concrete implementation classes - this is of course rather tedious.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
